The forces of the mega strike gather
The unions of the League and the National Association of Workers&#39; Councils will set up their strike committee on Friday, which will be responsible for coordinating the indefinite strike on Monday.
On Saturday, a general protest meeting will be held and on Monday, the day of the final vote on the law relating to health funds, the strike will begin.
This action will certainly cause major traffic jams because rail traffic will be almost completely stopped and the employees of BKV (public transport company) will also go on strike until 1 p.m.
The Unions of the league will make known, Friday afternoon, the details of their strike on Monday, organized with the National Association of Workers&#39; Councils.
The LIGA - MOSZ strike committee will also be constituted, it will serve as coordinator of Monday&#39;s actions.
Saturday, a general assembly of protest will be held and, from Monday, the organizations joining has the strike will stop work for an indefinite period if they do not manage to find an agreement with the government.
This means that the date of the end of the strike, from the day of the vote in parliament on the law relating to health funds, is not defined.
If the National Assembly does not adopt the law on health funds, the unions will immediately withdraw the call for a strike.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, the strike committees will meet and decide what action to take.
According to Monday&#39;s agenda for the National Assembly, it is likely that the vote on the law relating to health funds will not take place until late evening, or even at night.
Due to the strike scheduled for Monday, major traffic jams are expected: the railways will stop work for an indefinite period and during the morning part of the public transport in Budapest and more than half of the companies Volán are in danger of being arrested.
At the same time, at different points in the country, half of the road will also be blocked.
Many trade unions and civil organizations have joined in the call for a strike, the list of which is constantly updated on the League&#39;s website.
Some organizations report going on strike for an indefinite period, others have declared a temporary work stoppage.
Until Thursday afternoon the MÁV (Hungarian Railways) and the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (VDSZSZ) failed to reach an agreement on minimum services, however, with the approach of Christmas, more and more people are taking the train.
According to current communications, Budapest public transport will be on strike from the start of service until 1 p.m., Budapest Airport between 7 a.m. and 9 a.m., the Industrial Unions of Electricity and Thermal Energy of the League will be on strike four hours, the Teachers&#39; Union and the Democratic Teachers&#39; Union called for a strike for 2 hours and from 2 to 8 hours respectively.
The National Association of Doctors will strike across the country alternately, the Union of Health and Social Sector Employees (EDDSZ) attached to the SZEF will carry out a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands, formulated by the League, demands that the government withdraw its proposal for health reform and submit a new concept to social debate.
The second demand requires that the new method of calculating the pension to be put in place from next year be introduced in several stages.
The third demand wants a guarantee, in terms of retirement before the legal age, which would make it possible to pass into the system the functions which deserve it before 2010.
The fourth reason for the action is the rejection by the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (VDSZSZ), attached to the Unions of the League, of the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport concerning secondary railway lines and the expectation of another proposal.
Political Capital: Hungarian Guard increased country risk
According to the Risk Analyzing Division of Political Capital (Risk Analyzing Division), the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed last August with the support of Jobbik Magyarországért Mozgalom (Movement for a better Hungary) increases, in several aspects, the risk politics of Hungary and the region.
In its &quot;risk warning&quot;, the company points out that, in connection with the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is already that &quot;in the short term aggressive ethnic clashes may occur as a result of the worsening of the ethnic tension already existing between the gypsy and non-gypsy population of Hungary”.
The research institute added that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard presumably aiming to provoke this situation is the main reason for this.
As they say, this is explained by one of the main shortcomings of the Hungarian political actors: &quot;the public actors passed the public debate on the Roma affair to the representatives of the radical and extreme political groupings which based a political strategy on the dispute between the Gypsies and the Hungarians”.
The problem is aggravated, normal dialogue becomes impossible, extremists are strengthened and the arrival of aggressive conflicts is more likely, they say.
However, according to the research institute, under the effect of the increased attention of the Hungarian and international media, the activity of the Hungarian Guard &quot;has significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, in particular with regard to trust in the stability and democratic maturity of the country&quot;.
