However, it seems rather that Kerviel is only a great player who wanted to equal his colleagues, and who, in addition, can in no way be considered incapable.
Unlike all major banking houses, he recognized the crisis in the US mortgage market in time.
&quot;He is fragile,&quot; suggested his superiors who reported him to the police.
