&quot;All I wanted was to make money for my bank,&quot; he claims in the deposition.
Last summer, he managed to take advantage of the American crisis to earn half a billion euros.
In fact, he sensed the opportunity early on in the year.
Reports began to emerge in February that so-called “sub-prime” mortgages, granted to low-income customers or those who had experienced repayment difficulties in the past, were having problems.
