Disputes between politicians interest the public much more than abrupt figures.
The national budgets of past socialist governments suffered from three ills that the current budget is unable to address at once:
The first being the significant share granted to the costs of mandates imposed by law, consisting not only of pensions, but also of social charges, adopted last year by the silent &quot;coalition&quot; of the ČSSD and KSČM parties.
The second being a deficit economy, a consequence of the first evil.
The third obstacle is constituted by the deficit of public finances, ie by the deficit of cities and municipalities.
