The $70 billion deficit projected for 2008 would be absolutely useless if previous governments had not squandered all the money they could.
If we really do not want the politicians in power to become mere bureaucrats, we must be patient and grant this fragile government coalition, aware that the State can only spend the equivalent of what it succeeds in levying in taxes and fiscal rights, the calm necessary for the preparation of new reform laws.
