The majority of visitors do not miss the most famous places.
So there is no need to write much about Varadero or Havana.
Otherwise remember that in the property of Hemingway, already mentioned, there is a museum and that whoever loves this writer should not miss the visit.
The Viňales Valley in the west of the island is one of the most picturesque corners of Cuba.
Exuberant vegetation grows there on limestone soil.
Mogotes, calcareous balloons and rocks rise in candle from the bottom of the valley, and, of the fertile ground having taken in their entrails, even its rotten rocks are covered with a very dense vegetable carpet.
The valley is where probably the best quality Cuban tobacco is grown.
You will be able to encounter the final form of this product if you visit one of the cigar factories in Havana.
Someone might also find it interesting that the Chilean episode of Major Zeman was filmed there.
Trinidad
Ancient city founded shortly after the Spaniards colonized the island.
It was the market, the slave trade and the sugar trade that brought him fame and wealth.
Wealth is embodied in the beauty and showcase character of this small town.
Koloniální španělská architektura, výrazně ovlivněná pozdějšími francouzskými osadníky, se za čtyři staletí téměřnezměnila.
Trinidad, located between the sea and the Escambray mountain range, is such a remote place that even in the 50s of the last century there was no road that would connect this region with the rest of the country.
This isolation allowed him to stay on the sidelines.
We weren&#39;t building anything, and that&#39;s why we weren&#39;t demolishing anything either, everyone was content to have a roof over their heads.
If you have more time in Trinidad than an afternoon, then it is also worth going to see interesting places in the surroundings, such as Playa Ancón beach or the Sugar Valley.
Then, in the evening, it is customary to go to the Casa de la Música which comes alive after sunset and where the music only dies down in the early morning.
baracoa
Some refer to this town located in the far east of Cuba as the most beautiful on the island.
This opinion is certainly already influenced by the path that leads to it.
The two roads leading there from Guantánamo must cross high and rugged mountains and pass through a landscape almost unmarked by human activity.
UNESCO has inscribed the Eastern Cuba reef, thanks to its intact landscape, on the World Heritage List.
The best chocolate is made there, in the church there is the cross of Christopher Columbus (in fact, it was created about a hundred years after Columbus&#39; journey) and from the hill where the old castle and the current hotel El Castillo, we see several table mountains, the most famous of which is El Yunque.
About coffee, rum, cigars, the Sierra Maestra mountain range, the Bay of Sows and Isla de Pinos island, the Tropicana cabaret, the sanctuary of Cuba&#39;s patron saint Caridad del Cobre, Santeria , African religions practiced by the descendants of former slaves, about all this one could fill a number of pages.
Only, as they say, it is better to see once.
