Then there are the maximum sources planned for the Czech Consolidation Agency, namely 13.3 billion crowns, the reserve of 10 billion for the payment of pensions, the financing of state annuity securities for 43 billion crowns and repayments of European Investment Bank loans amounting to 1.8 billion crowns.
