With this sentence Paolo Vasile, a delegated adviser of Telecinco, yesterday expressed his satisfaction, at the close of the stock market, when he found that the channel he leads doubled the value of its rival, Antena 3.
A single aspect tarnished his joy: &#39;what hurts me is not the fact that we have increased more but that we have decreased less&#39;, he affirmed.
However, he emphasized that in a weak market &#39;we fell less&#39;.
Telecinco ended the day yesterday with an increase of 2.54%.
This gain stabilizes its loss at 15.66% for a year.
The stock market value of the company controlled by Mediaset (with 52% of the capital) and announced by Vocento (13% more) thus reached 4,488.88 million euros, according to data from Bloomberg.
Its rival Antena 3, which yielded 1.52% yesterday and which has accumulated a drop of 40.5% since January, costs half, 2,193.46 million.
The value of other communication companies listed on the stock exchange amounts to 3.571 million in the case of Sogecable; 2,518.53 million in that of Prisa (the publisher of Cinco Días) and 1,779 million in that of Vocento.
According to Vasile, the comparison with Antenna 3 is due to the fact that &#39;we are talking about two similar companies.
The relative fact represents what we are able to do, in the same market, at what price and how we make it profitable in terms of audience&#39;.
Telecinco announced last week that it plans to become this year the first television channel to surpass 1,000 million in gross advertising revenue, as assured Giuseppe Tringali, the delegated adviser of Telecinco and Publiespaña, the subsidiary that manages advertising of the group.
For this announced data to be real, the television channel should register for the current financial year an increase of 3.6% in its billing for advertising compared to the 965.4 million for the 2006 financial year.
For its part, Antenne 3&#39;s net billing increased by 1.6% in the first nine months of the financial year (to reach 734.4 million) while net television revenues increased by 0 .7% (630.4 million).
One of the factors that analysts point to for the better relative evolution of Telecinco on the stock market is the important payout that it has maintained until now: in 2006, the company chaired by Alejandro Echevarría distributed 100% of the profit between its shareholders.
Vasile assures that, although it is early to make a decision, this ratio could vary after the purchase of 33% of Endemol and in association with Mediaset.
&#39;We have the official commitment to give a minimum of 50%, although we have always declared much more.
This year, I hope that we will be able to make happy our shareholders, those to whom we have already given titles with the 33% of Endemol&#39;.
According to analysts, the market is currently showing signs of fatigue.
Lehman Brothers recently cut its profit estimates for Telecinco in 2008 to 4% and in 2009 to 7%.
This is due, they explain, to the decline in projected revenue growth from 10.5% to 8.4% in 2008 and from 5.5% to 5.1% in 2009.
This same company reduced the earnings forecast for Antenne 3 to 4.5% in 2008 and 7.5% in 2009.
