What insurance is right for me?
Motor insurance, which covers the driver against possible claims, involves a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of the driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or the use to which it is put, among other things.
Having a car is the main thing.
Y es que, escoger el seguro de automóvil adecuado es incluso más difícil que elegir el modelo de vehículo.
And it is that, to choose the adequate automobile insurance, is even more difficult than to choose the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is materialized by an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in exchange it becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a claim.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of the driving license, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or the use we make of it, among other things.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so the higher the probability of suffering an accident, the higher the odds to be paid.
It is for this reason that people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, since statistics show that these people have a lower loss rate due to their caution.
Similarly, using censuses, companies have concluded that married people tend to have fewer crashes than single drivers.
The use made of the vehicle will influence the frequency, and therefore the probability of having an accident.
By increasing the frequency the probabilities increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the price of the premium.
This is why the driver must carefully study the situation to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
Here we will expose the most significant variables when choosing one or another type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers him a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face various disadvantages when signing a contract with insurance at an affordable price, such as low driving experience and the age of the driving licence.
Although the ideal way to be well insured is all-risk insurance, other more economical options exist.
The most far-sighted drivers can opt for all-risk insurance with deductible, so that they obtain the coverage of all-risk insurance but at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays part of the amount of the claim.
&quot;The part of the amount of the claim that the customer pays will be established according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount will be&quot;, specifies Luis Noguera, the manager in Spain of First Europa, online insurance mediator. .
Another option is extended third party insurance, whereby the customer provides protection against damage caused to third parties, but not for damage caused to his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
An advice.
If you are under 25, try to be careful and avoid claims as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus, which may reduce the price of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction of the base rate that the company has.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic rate.
&quot;The bonuses and sanctions will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses&quot;, clarifies Noguera.
Beyond the age of 25, it becomes easier for drivers when signing a contract with insurance, since the loss rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
It is for this reason that it is preferable to choose all-risk insurance with a deductible.
&quot;Normally young people cannot take advantage of the experience previously acquired after an accident&quot;, assures the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once passed the &#39; fear of the novice&#39;.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is preferable that he negotiates comprehensive insurance, as long as his economic situation allows him to do so.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be the people with the lowest loss ratio, because the increases will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be all-risk insurance with deductible (which may be 300 euros), or extended third-party insurance from the third year of the vehicle&#39;s life when the insured has a high level of bonus. .
&quot;They have a more relaxed conduct and they have greater purchasing power to allow themselves the luxury of assuming a greater quantity of franchises&quot;, judge Luis Noguera.
For retirees, all-risk insurance with deductible is preferable (being this of 150 euros), or extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver against possible claims, but also because it represents a major expense, which is why it It is fundamental to properly study the insurance that best suits us according to our personal situation.
